text: my name is Neve my role as an account
manager on the AWS public sector team
here in Dublin is to be the first point
to contact for our customers into the
organization and I acted almost as an
advocate for our customers to find the
right resources for them and the right
support at the right time my background
is in the non-profit sector I worked for
Charities and also on the agency side as
well for 10 years one common struggle I
saw across all the other organizations
that I worked with was that technology
wasn't being seen or been used as an
enabler technology and limitations of
systems were dictating processes and
policies rather than the other way
around and then when I came across the
non-profit team in AWS I really wanted
to get the opportunity to work with
non-profit and other public sector
organizations as well to to change how
they see technology and see it as an
enabler I don't have a tech background
so coming in working in a big Tech was
initially a bit scary and I'm conscious
that it can't come across as a bit scary
to people but it's not especially as a
woman working in techs and people can be
nervous about going for a position like
that honestly out of everywhere I've
ever worked I've never felt more equal
and respected as a woman and the tech
part kind of just
I just woke up one day and understood it
I really love working at AWS because you
are constantly surrounded with some of
the smartest people that you've ever met
it's a constant challenge but also
really inspiring and you learn a huge
amount as well and I've never worked
